The paper discusses attribute-based access control (ABAC) languages, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of lattice-based decision sets, which falls under the category of lattice theory (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper proposes a new authorization language, which involves programming language concepts (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the advantages of the proposed language within the framework of XACML, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE).
